When working with Sql.DateAdd for Postgres you can only pass constant as second argument:

``` csharp
var thisWorksNow = db.Orders.Where(x => Sql.DateAdd(Sql.DateParts.Hour, 3, x.Date) > date).ToList();
```

But you can't pass variable. This patch fixes this:

``` csharp
var hours = 3;
var thisWillWorkAfterFix = db.Orders.Where(x => Sql.DateAdd(Sql.DateParts.Hour, hours, x.Date) > date).ToList();
```

